<item>
            <title>[HIVE-24291] Compaction Cleaner prematurely cleans up deltas</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-24291</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-23107&quot; title=&quot;Remove MIN_HISTORY_LEVEL table&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-23107&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-23107&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the cleaner can clean up deltas that are still used by running queries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TxnId 1-5 writes to a partition, all commits&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Compactor starts with txnId=6&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Long running query starts with txnId=7, it sees txnId=6 as open in its snapshot&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Compaction commits&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cleaner runs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Previously min_history_level table would have prevented the Cleaner to delete the deltas1-5 until txnId=7 is open, but now they will be deleted and the long running query may fail if its tries to access the files.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Solution could be to not run the cleaner until any txn is open that was opened before the compaction was committed (CQ_NEXT_TXN_ID)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
